data.name: Granbull

attacks.name: Timid Tackle
attacks.text: Granbull does 20 damage to itself. Switch Granbull with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Chomp
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Granbull.

data.flavorText: Because its fangs are too heavy, it always keeps its head tilted down. However, its bite is powerful.

attacks.name: Double Stomp
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

data.flavorText: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.

abilities.name: Intimidating Fang
abilities.text: As long as Granbull is your Active Pokémon, any damage done by an opponent's attack is reduced by 10 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Crushing Blow
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Double Lariat
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

data.name: Granbull

attacks.name: Raging Charge
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Granbull. Then, Granbull does 20 damage to itself.

data.flavorText: It is actually timid and easily spooked. If attacked, it flails about to fend off its attacker.

data.name: Granbull

attacks.name: Daunt
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Rage
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Granbull.

data.flavorText: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.

data.name: Granbull

attacks.name: Jaw Lock
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

data.flavorText: Although it's popular with young people, Granbull is timid and sensitive, so it's totally incompetent as a watchdog.

data.name: Granbull

attacks.name: Dark Clamp
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Fight Back
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 80 more damage.

data.flavorText: More timid than Snubbull, this Pokémon is doted on by young people amused at the contrast between its looks and its attitude.

attacks.name: Fling
attacks.text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon, if any. (Do the damage before switching the Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Startling Bark
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 3 random cards from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals those cards and shuffles them into his or her deck.

attacks.name: Tantrum
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Confused.

data.flavorText: It can make most any Pokémon run away simply by opening its mouth wide to reveal its big fangs.
